opicID=573.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The passing of our Tigerlilly of the North</span><hr size=1> Dia has left the building.<br>
<br>
After a good 18 months of romping, stomping and general good-heartedness, Dia has retired from Asheron's Call.<br>
<br>
Thank you as always M'lady for your kindness, strong heart and spirit, and frankly just for being yourself. We have all enjoyed the many hunts, quests and hours of fun. There will always be just one Dia, fearless, always in the lead and just a little crazy - just as it should be!<br>
<br>
Please remember to keep us informed as to your ingame whereabouts, you never know when we might all decide to join you in some other world, place or time.<br>
<br>
Until we meet again, Thanks and Happy Mothers Day!<br>
<br>
FTFL guild, Leafcull <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uceleroy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celeroy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0> at: 5/12/01 6:31:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Crow</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/12/01 8:22:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> &lt;sigh&gt;</span><hr size=1> I'm just sorry that I couldn't be there to see her one last time. Be good Dia ... you will be missed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/13/01 12:29:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The passing of our Tigerlilly of the North</span><hr size=1> I'm so sorry I missed you Friday night as well Dia. First night I haven't played in a couple of weeks too, it figures.<br>
<br>
I'm so sorry to see you go, but all good things come to an end I guess. You won't be forgotten, that's for sure. We have had some great adventures together in Dereth, and I hope we get a chance to have some more in some other world. Let us know what your next world will be, wherever and whenever it is I'll be there!<br>
<br>
Fair seas and following winds, my friend.<br>
<br>
- Ghar (missing Dia already) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0> at: 5/13/01 2:11:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dia>Dia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/13/01 9:26:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> games</span><hr size=1> Thank you for your good words! I don't know where I will be next. For now, I will upgrade my knowledge of computer games. I have downloaded some demos just to see what I like or not. Lesson one, I don't like first person shooter games. Now, lets see if I can find something I like.<br>
<br>
A question to you computer wizards: what is the cheapest way to upgrade my computer. Can I just buy a mother board with CPU and memory and keep the rest? (plug in my hard disk, cd-rom, modem, monitor etc...) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/13/01 11:39:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: games</span><hr size=1> LOL, well, the reason I missed you Friday night was that I screwed up my computer trying to install Windows 2000. So I'm not sure I'm the best guy to be giving computer advice! But here's my two cents:<br>
<br>
If you buy a new motherboard and processor, you'll probably need to buy some faster RAM too, and maybe a new case. My old Dell used a non-standard case, so I had to buy a new case when I replaced the motherboard. If you have a really old video card, you might end up wanting to replace that to take advantage of the faster processor, but you can always do that later. Other than that, all your other components should work fine.<br>
<br>
Here's a couple of links that have some good tips on upgrading:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.pcguide.com/">www.pcguide.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://arstechnica.com/">arstechnica.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ulusarl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lusarl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/15/01 2:07:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: games</span><hr size=1>  I am saddened to see you go Dia. You have always been the rough tough no holds barred fighting female that Harl has just ner been able to keep up with. But I understand about your decision to do so. We all have our own paths to follow an I can sincerely say that from the deapths of my heart I hope our paths will cross again someday soon. Until then my thoughts will always be with you. May the forest Lords protect you and your travels be well. <br>
                                With best wishes;<br>
                 Harl. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dia>Dia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/18/01 11:27:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> thanks</span><hr size=1> Thank you Harl, I wish we will see us again in an other world.<br>
Thank you Ghar for those links. I've used them but must admit that I found this really complicated. I will work on this and find a way to upgrade this computer without going over my budget.<br>
An other question: Celeron or PIII? Celeron is nice because it reminds me of celeroy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and it's half the price. But is it good for gaming? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/18/01 3:03:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thanks</span><hr size=1> LOL, just remember, this is coming from a guy who spent last night ripping out hard drives from his machine in a desperate attempt to get it working again after my last attempt at upgrading! (I tried adding a third hard drive for no good reason, and I guess my power supply didn't approve of the extra work it had to do.)<br>
<br>
I'm not sure how Celeron's and P3's compare these days, but you might want to take a look at AMD's processors as well. Everything I've read says the new AMD Thunderbirds are as good as a P3 and considerably cheaper. I had always used Intels, but I switched to a 1GHz Thunderbird this winter. AMD also makes a cheaper processor called a Duron that I guess is their equivalent to a Celeron. This stuff does get so confusing though, it's impossible to keep up on everything.<br>
<br>
Here's another link that might be helpful, where they pick out the components for what they call a &quot;budget&quot; gaming system:  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.sharkyextreme.com/theguide/value_game_pc/">www.sharkyextreme.com/the...e_game_pc/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ulusarl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lusarl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/19/01 8:58:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thanks</span><hr size=1> Might want to be careful. I have had many friends that have had a bad time of it when trying to match anything other than a Nvidia Geoforce graphics card to the amd thunderbird chipset. Don't get me wrong it is a very good chip but don't plan on using a radeon graphics card with it. I am unsuire if they have fixed the conflict problem in the thunderbirds yet as this happened quite a while ago butits just something to be aware of. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dia>Dia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/19/01 9:08:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> computers</span><hr size=1> Wow! thanks! With this last link and all your friendly advises, I'll know more about game computers than the vendor does. Hehehe I belive thats a good thing.<br>
(Dia's computer knowledge is now raised to 126 base!) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showMessage?topicID=575.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showMessage?topicID=569.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=573.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=573.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.threadControl?topicID=573.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=573.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=573.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub10.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="forgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral">General<option value="forgottentruthforeignlegionlinks">Links<option value="forgottentruthfo